$$
\zeta(s) = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^s}
$$
(for complex $s$ with Re$(s)>1$, analytically continued elsewhere).

**Non-trivial zeros** lie in the critical strip $0 < $ Re$(s) < 1$. The **Riemann Hypothesis (RH)** states they all have Re$(s) = 1/2$ (the critical line).

