- ...

These zeros **encode prime distribution** through the explicit formula:
$$
\pi(x) \approx \text{Li}(x) - \sum_{\rho} \frac{\text{Li}(x^\rho)}{\rho} + \dots
$$
where $\rho$ are the zeros. Prime gaps fluctuate according to the oscillatory contribution from these zeros.

